# Plan Before Code

- Before writing any feature, outline the approach: which files will be created/modified, what the key design decisions are, and how you will verify correctness
- If the task is ambiguous, ask clarifying questions before writing code
- Break work into small, testable increments that can each be committed independently
- When multiple approaches exist, present trade-offs (complexity, performance, maintainability) and recommend one with rationale
- Reference @PROMPT.md for the original assessment requirements -- do not drift from them
- After planning, confirm the approach before proceeding to implementation
